<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-55-1018 </DOCNO><TEXT>Using two different methods to calculate the relative difference betweenthe central nuclear density and the nuclear matter value as a functionof A/sup -1/3/, we have proved new theorems which are in the spirit ofthe ''{sigma}=0'' theorem. It is also shown that, contrarily to the ''{sigma}=0''theorem, these theorems are not verified for all modes of compression.</TEXT></DOC>